    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — discerning the author's intent in its original context and its place in the canon. Joshua 12 is not a narrative chapter but a formal legal-doxological document. Its movements follow the chapter's two-part structure and its cumulative rhetorical logic. Each pericope rewards theological attention precisely because the genre resists it: the reader who pushes past the geography and the list will find one of the Old Testament's most compact statements about the nature of divine faithfulness.",
